I'll tell him you're here

807
01:03:30,540 --> 01:03:31,131
Oh, I thank you

808
01:03:31,207 --> 01:03:31,730
Alright... boy, let's go

809
01:03:31,808 --> 01:03:34,106
Good morning, Mrs. Strauss... good morning

810
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:35,075
Come on, Kienzl

811
01:03:35,111 --> 01:03:38,774
Mr. Kienzl, please... I've been promoted

812
01:03:56,299 --> 01:04:01,100
'You told me you loved me
when we were young one day'

813
01:04:02,104 --> 01:04:04,436
Remember when you told me, Johann?

814
01:04:04,974 --> 01:04:07,636
That's the most beautiful day
of my life

815
01:04:07,910 --> 01:04:09,935
Please, Poldi... I'm very busy now

816
01:04:10,379 --> 01:04:13,542
Johann, you must take time
for your coffee

817
01:04:13,616 --> 01:04:14,947
Alright

818
01:04:17,687 --> 01:04:20,155
'You told me you loved me'

819
01:04:20,556 --> 01:04:23,218
What makes you think of it now, Johann?

820
01:04:23,292 --> 01:04:24,850
Poldi, can't you see I'm working?

821
01:04:24,927 --> 01:04:26,690
Why ask a silly question like that?

822
01:04:27,129 --> 01:04:29,029
I write a song as it comes to me... 

823
01:04:29,065 --> 01:04:31,397
out of... out of my inspiration... 

824
01:04:31,467 --> 01:04:34,231
out of everything... 
out of heaven knows what

825
01:04:34,303 --> 01:04:38,467
I guess so, Johann... 
drink your coffee before it's cold

826
01:04:43,512 --> 01:04:44,740
Cold?

827
01:04:44,847 --> 01:04:46,109
It's scolding

828
01:04:46,215 --> 01:04:48,012
I'll cool it for you

829
01:04:49,118 --> 01:04:52,053
Johann, don't you think you should
lie down a while?

830
01:04:52,121 --> 01:04:54,817
You must be tired after being
out of night

831
01:04:54,891 --> 01:04:56,791
What are you driving at?

832
01:04:56,926 --> 01:04:58,518
Can't you see I'm working?

833
01:04:58,594 --> 01:04:59,424
Why should I be tired?

834
01:04:59,495 --> 01:05:01,190
I worked before, didn't I?

835
01:05:01,631 --> 01:05:04,657
Oh, Johann... I won't disturb you anymore

836
01:05:04,800 --> 01:05:05,994
Now you're hurt

837
01:05:06,269 --> 01:05:07,429
No, I'm not hurt

838
01:05:07,536 --> 01:05:08,628
You are

839
01:05:08,838 --> 01:05:15,073
No, it's only... Johann, you're so crossed

840
01:05:15,177 --> 01:05:16,735
since you come home

841
01:05:16,812 --> 01:05:18,370
You didn't... 

842
01:05:18,447 --> 01:05:21,610
I don't expect you to kiss me
if you don't feel like it

843
01:05:22,051 --> 01:05:24,713
But you didn't talk to me

844
01:05:24,787 --> 01:05:27,779
Johann, what's the matter with you?

845
01:05:27,890 --> 01:05:30,154
You're imagining things, that's all

846
01:05:30,226 --> 01:05:31,716
I think it's you ought to lie down... 

847
01:05:31,794 --> 01:05:33,489
you're pale and tired

848
01:05:33,663 --> 01:05:36,894
You know I can't sleep when
you're not at home

849
01:05:36,966 --> 01:05:38,558
Now, that has got to stop

850
01:05:38,634 --> 01:05:40,295
Why can't you sleep when I'm not home?

851
01:05:40,836 --> 01:05:44,829
It's only natural for a wife who
can't sleep when her husband is out... 

852
01:05:44,907 --> 01:05:47,068
in danger maybe

853
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:50,245
Why do I talk about things like that?

854
01:05:50,313 --> 01:05:52,440
You're not going to stay out anymore

855
01:05:52,515 --> 01:05:55,609
We don't have revolution everyday... 
thanks heaven

856
01:05:55,685 --> 01:05:57,585
What does revolution have to do
with it?

857
01:05:57,653 --> 01:05:58,881
The revolution is the only thing that

858
01:05:58,955 --> 01:06:00,582
can keep a man out once in a while?

859
01:06:00,656 --> 01:06:01,645
Things happen to a man

860
01:06:01,724 --> 01:06:04,158
Things... you can't foresee anything

861
01:06:04,226 --> 01:06:05,989
Besides, I'm not your slave... 
not your prisoner... 

862
01:06:06,095 --> 01:06:07,790
and we're not chained to each other

863
01:06:07,863 --> 01:06:09,990
Don't shout at me, please

864
01:06:10,066 --> 01:06:13,331
If you've something on your mind... 
if you've something want to tell me... 

865
01:06:13,436 --> 01:06:14,801
tell me

866
01:06:14,870 --> 01:06:16,997
But don't shout at me

867
01:06:17,073 --> 01:06:18,870
If you don't want to tell me,

868
01:06:18,941 --> 01:06:21,102
you don't need to make excuses for yourself

869
01:06:21,177 --> 01:06:23,304
You don't need to act like this

870
01:06:23,846 --> 01:06:28,579
If you want to stay out at night... 
you're free to do so

871
01:06:28,651 --> 01:06:32,985
But you must leave me free to worry
about you if I like

872
01:06:33,055 --> 01:06:35,785
You must respect my feelings

873
01:06:35,958 --> 01:06:39,951
To be the wife of Johann Strauss
is not a little thing

874
01:06:40,062 --> 01:06:42,724
I've tried to be won'thy of it

875
01:06:42,832 --> 01:06:45,027
I'm very proud of it

876
01:06:45,101 --> 01:06:48,036
I won't let anyone shout at me

877
01:06:48,104 --> 01:06:50,664
for your sake as well as mine

878
01:06:55,444 --> 01:06:57,309
Forgiver me, Poldi

879
01:06:57,413 --> 01:06:59,847
I always seem to be shouting at you

880
01:07:00,716 --> 01:07:02,741
I don't know what's the matter with me

881
01:07:03,085 --> 01:07:06,953
I wouldn't change you... nothing on you... 

882
01:07:07,056 --> 01:07:10,253
not even your moods... your temper

883
01:07:10,726 --> 01:07:13,456
because I know you must be like this

884
01:07:13,562 --> 01:07:15,621
to be you

885
01:07:16,132 --> 01:07:18,259
Alright then, let's go away

886
01:07:18,334 --> 01:07:21,098
It'll be better... better for both of us

887
01:07:21,170 --> 01:07:23,934
Let's forget we ever saw Vienna

888
01:07:24,740 --> 01:07:26,207
Forget Vienna?

889
01:07:26,308 --> 01:07:31,245
L... I mean... there're too many
distractions here

890
01:07:31,814 --> 01:07:34,305
But we live here, Johann

891
01:07:34,417 --> 01:07:38,615
We live in a lovely new home and
all our friends

892
01:07:38,687 --> 01:07:39,949
Don't you want to travel?

893
01:07:40,022 --> 01:07:41,853
Don't you want to see the world?

894
01:07:41,957 --> 01:07:43,083
Of course, I do

895
01:07:43,159 --> 01:07:44,820
If you... so... 

896
01:07:44,894 --> 01:07:46,555
Alright then, darling... that's settled

897
01:07:46,629 --> 01:07:49,757
Now you start packing your things and
I'll make the arrangements

898
01:07:49,865 --> 01:07:52,390
We can't just pack up and go

899
01:07:52,468 --> 01:07:54,868
We have a lot of things to attend to

900
01:07:54,904 --> 01:07:56,132
No, nonsense

901
01:07:56,205 --> 01:07:57,638
Then we go without attending to them

902
01:07:57,706 --> 01:07:59,196
Poldi, when you think of going... 

903
01:07:59,275 --> 01:08:00,367
that's the time to go

904
01:08:00,443 --> 01:08:03,810
But Mr. Hofbauer downstairs and boys... 

905
01:08:04,180 --> 01:08:07,206
Oh, they are... fine

906
01:08:07,750 --> 01:08:08,580
Come on... let's go

907
01:08:08,651 --> 01:08:10,710
I'll tell them we're going right away

908
01:08:25,501 --> 01:08:30,996
Ah... Strauss

909
01:08:32,741 --> 01:08:35,710
Kienzl, will you stop that for a minute?

910
01:08:35,778 --> 01:08:37,177
You wrote it

911
01:08:38,147 --> 01:08:39,842
Alright... I'm sorry

912
01:08:40,583 --> 01:08:43,643
Well, Poldi has something say to you

913
01:08:43,719 --> 01:08:44,276
Huh?

914
01:08:44,353 --> 01:08:46,480
Go on, Poldi... tell them the good news

915
01:08:46,555 --> 01:08:47,749
Good news?

916
01:08:47,823 --> 01:08:49,017
Right

917
01:08:50,292 --> 01:08:52,453
We're going to leave Vienna

918
01:08:52,528 --> 01:08:53,324
What?

919
01:08:53,395 --> 01:08:54,054
Immediately

920
01:08:54,163 --> 01:08:54,993
What for?

921
01:08:55,064 --> 01:08:55,621
What's happening?

922
01:08:55,698 --> 01:08:56,289
Why are you leaving?

923
01:08:56,365 --> 01:08:58,128
Why he can't leave Vienna
if he wants to?

924
01:08:58,167 --> 01:08:59,225
Vienna is not the world

925
01:08:59,301 --> 01:09:00,962
and he doesn't owe Vienna anything

926
01:09:01,036 --> 01:09:03,197
Vienna owes him more than
it can ever pay

927
01:09:03,239 --> 01:09:04,171
What becomes of me... ?

928
01:09:04,206 --> 01:09:05,400
Why the fuss?

929
01:09:05,474 --> 01:09:07,066
Why are you all upset about?

930
01:09:07,143 --> 01:09:08,838
The musician ought to travel

931
01:09:08,911 --> 01:09:11,038
Poldi and I have made up our minds

932
01:09:11,113 --> 01:09:13,240
It's all as well... we'll be back someday

933
01:09:13,315 --> 01:09:16,807
Yes, we've planned it, that's all

934
01:09:17,153 --> 01:09:21,886
After all, we never had our
real honeymoon

935
01:09:26,128 --> 01:09:27,857
By the way, did you get my march?

936
01:09:27,930 --> 01:09:28,555
No

937
01:09:28,631 --> 01:09:29,154
What do you mean?

938
01:09:29,231 --> 01:09:30,163
Didrt you get my message?

939
01:09:30,199 --> 01:09:31,097
I haven't got a march

940
01:09:31,167 --> 01:09:31,826
What have you got?

941
01:09:31,901 --> 01:09:32,526
Nothing

942
01:09:32,568 --> 01:09:33,193
Nothing?

943
01:09:33,302 --> 01:09:36,237
Yes... there's a new piece you've composed

944
01:09:36,372 --> 01:09:39,239
Yes, Poldi, it... but it's not ready yet

945
01:09:39,308 --> 01:09:40,138
Look here, Strauss

946
01:09:40,209 --> 01:09:41,608
Has Shanon made you some offer?

947
01:09:41,644 --> 01:09:42,804
Remember you have a contract with me

948
01:09:42,845 --> 01:09:43,777
for everything you write

949
01:09:43,812 --> 01:09:46,212
Mr. Hofbauer, you know he won't do
a thing like that

950
01:09:46,282 --> 01:09:48,546
If he doesn't want to play... 
you mustrt urge him

951
01:09:48,584 --> 01:09:50,347
I never urged him... 
just temperamental, that's all

952
01:09:50,386 --> 01:09:52,286
He wants to be temperamental... 
but he took my 1,000 golden... 

953
01:09:52,354 --> 01:09:58,122
For every golden... alright, I'll get it

954
01:09:58,227 --> 01:10:03,028
Johann, you have it in your pocket... here

955
01:10:05,167 --> 01:10:08,568
Yes... go ahead, Kienzl

956
01:10:08,637 --> 01:10:10,696
Sure... let's start

957
01:10:10,773 --> 01:10:11,705
Alright... let's take places

958
01:10:11,774 --> 01:10:13,036
Come on... sit down, boys

959
01:10:13,108 --> 01:10:14,268
Come on, don't keep waiting
while you listen

960
01:10:14,343 --> 01:10:15,002
He keeps waiting

961
01:10:15,110 --> 01:10:15,906
You keep waiting

962
01:10:15,978 --> 01:10:16,672
All I have to do is waiting

963
01:10:16,745 --> 01:10:18,679
You don't have to wait, Mr. Hofbauer

964
01:10:18,714 --> 01:10:19,840
Vienna is a free city, you know

965
01:10:19,915 --> 01:10:20,813
Oh, I see

966
01:10:20,883 --> 01:10:22,214
The whole world is waiting
for this waltz

967
01:10:22,284 --> 01:10:23,444
Why shouldn't you wait?

968
01:10:23,485 --> 01:10:26,045
Yes, you should... that's right

969
01:11:51,940 --> 01:11:53,134
Bravo... 

970
01:11:53,175 --> 01:11:53,937
Carla

971
01:11:54,009 --> 01:11:55,909
Madam Donner

972
01:11:55,978 --> 01:11:57,969
How do you do, Madam?

973
01:11:58,314 --> 01:12:00,714
It was beautiful, Mr. Strauss

974
01:12:01,383 --> 01:12:02,873
Thank you, Madam

975
01:12:02,951 --> 01:12:04,646
I have great news

976
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:07,746
You've been commissioned to try another
opera in the Imperial Theatre

977
01:12:07,823 --> 01:12:08,915
for me to sing

978
01:12:08,991 --> 01:12:11,289
Oh, wonderful

979
01:12:11,360 --> 01:12:12,759
Madam, you're incomparable

980
01:12:12,828 --> 01:12:16,628
Cheer, everybody

981
01:12:16,765 --> 01:12:18,960
Well, Johann, aren't you pleased?

982
01:12:19,435 --> 01:12:21,665
Yes, of course, Madam... of course

983
01:12:21,737 --> 01:12:23,329
Madam, will you permit me?

984
01:12:23,372 --> 01:12:26,239
Poldi, this is my wife

985
01:12:26,742 --> 01:12:29,734
I'm very glad to know you, Mrs. Strauss

986
01:12:29,812 --> 01:12:32,007
I've been very anxious to meet you

987
01:12:32,081 --> 01:12:33,912
This is an honor, Madam... 

988
01:12:33,982 --> 01:12:36,473
thank you, you're very kind

989
01:12:36,552 --> 01:12:40,079
I'm very grateful, Madam, but... 
I can't accept

990
01:12:40,923 --> 01:12:43,323
We've made our plans... 
we're leaving Vienna

991
01:12:43,392 --> 01:12:43,881
What's the matter, Strauss?

992
01:12:43,959 --> 01:12:44,721
Are you insane?

993
01:12:44,793 --> 01:12:47,284
Johann... for all our sake

994
01:12:47,930 --> 01:12:49,761
You must persuade him, Mrs. Strauss

995
01:12:49,865 --> 01:12:51,992
This is no time for pride, isn't it?

996
01:12:53,135 --> 01:12:54,727
You're right, Madam... 

997
01:12:54,837 --> 01:12:56,737
this is no time for pride

998
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:00,836
You must stay, Johann

999
01:13:00,909 --> 01:13:05,869
You mustrt miss an opportunity
like this... without considering

1000
01:13:05,948 --> 01:13:08,746
To write an opera for the Imperial Theatre,

1001
01:13:08,817 --> 01:13:12,753
this is what we... what you wanted all the time... 

1002
01:13:12,821 --> 01:13:14,721
what you've dreamed for

1003
01:13:14,890 --> 01:13:21,352
A NEW OPERA

1004
01:14:49,751 --> 01:14:52,686
Shall I put this away, Mrs. Strauss?

1005
01:14:53,255 --> 01:14:56,520
Poldi darling, maybe you'll change
your mind

1006
01:14:59,294 --> 01:15:02,320
No, Mama... out the dress away, Anna

1007
01:15:06,835 --> 01:15:08,666
I don't want to nag you, Poldi

1008
01:15:08,737 --> 01:15:10,534
But after all, you really belong there

1009
01:15:10,606 --> 01:15:11,766
What will people think?

1010
01:15:11,807 --> 01:15:15,265
Mother, please... I'm too excited

1011
01:15:15,344 --> 01:15:16,971
I'm so happy here with you and

1012
01:15:17,079 --> 01:15:20,845
we can pray for him with all my heart and thoughts

1013
01:15:22,017 --> 01:15:24,781
After the performance, we can celebrate

1014
01:15:28,223 --> 01:15:31,283
I believe that carriage is stopping
in front of our house

1015
01:15:33,428 --> 01:15:35,225
Yes, it is

1016
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:40,325
Johann has sent for me

1017
01:15:40,402 --> 01:15:43,565
Be careful... be careful of the stairs... 
Poldi

1018
01:15:49,311 --> 01:15:51,370
I'll open the door, Anna

1019
01:15:53,482 --> 01:15:55,245
Is Mrs. Strauss in?

1020
01:15:55,717 --> 01:15:57,446
I'm Mrs. Strauss

1021
01:15:57,853 --> 01:15:59,844
I'm Count Hobenfried

1022
01:15:59,955 --> 01:16:01,547
My husband isn't here

1023
01:16:01,623 --> 01:16:05,525
I know... 
could I speak to you for a moment?

1024
01:16:05,861 --> 01:16:07,260
Come in, Sir

1025
01:16:07,563 --> 01:16:08,996
Thank you

1026
01:16:14,469 --> 01:16:16,437
I shouldn't detain you for long, Madam

1027
01:16:16,538 --> 01:16:18,369
Thank you, no... 

1028
01:16:19,007 --> 01:16:23,171
Perhaps something what I've to say
is known to you

1029
01:16:24,079 --> 01:16:30,678
l... Madam, I'm in love with Carla Donner

1030
01:16:31,219 --> 01:16:35,622
What's that you want to speak to me
about, Count Hobenfried?

1031
01:16:36,425 --> 01:16:38,893
Madam, for some time now,

1032
01:16:38,961 --> 01:16:43,955
Madam Carla and your husband had... 
had been infatuated with each other

1033
01:16:44,499 --> 01:16:46,729
During all these weeks of rehearsals... 

1034
01:16:46,802 --> 01:16:49,293
they've been together constantly and... 

1035
01:16:49,371 --> 01:16:52,204
I don't understand one word
you're saying

1036
01:16:52,274 --> 01:16:54,765
You don't know what all Vienna is... 

1037
01:16:57,879 --> 01:17:00,006
forgive me, Madam

1038
01:17:00,082 --> 01:17:02,846
I understand what you feel... 
Count Hobenfried

1039
01:17:02,918 --> 01:17:03,885
But you're mistaken

1040
01:17:03,986 --> 01:17:05,817
There's nothing wrong, I swear

1041
01:17:06,888 --> 01:17:09,220
I give you my word

1042
01:17:11,259 --> 01:17:14,922
You know, of course... 
there's always this rumor

1043
01:17:17,666 --> 01:17:19,861
Madam, for your sake,

1044
01:17:19,935 --> 01:17:22,062
I'd not presume for the sake of mine

1045
01:17:22,170 --> 01:17:25,435
But for his sake, you should stop this
at once

1046
01:17:25,540 --> 01:17:27,940
I've no right in this matter, Madam

1047
01:17:28,010 --> 01:17:30,604
You're his wife... you have

1048
01:17:30,679 --> 01:17:31,771
She'll destroy him

1049
01:17:31,847 --> 01:17:33,337
They'll destroy each other

1050
01:17:33,415 --> 01:17:36,350
She's the woman of violent feelings... 
strange whims

1051
01:17:36,418 --> 01:17:38,511
and irresistible impulses

1052
01:17:38,553 --> 01:17:39,645
Mr. Strauss is not for the man

1053
01:17:39,721 --> 01:17:41,450
to cope with this extraordinary person

1054
01:17:41,523 --> 01:17:42,217
He'll be ruined

1055
01:17:42,324 --> 01:17:43,313
I beg you

1056
01:17:43,392 --> 01:17:48,625
Madam, you must face the facts
unless you're willing to surrender

1057
01:17:49,131 --> 01:17:51,998
What I can see is so dear to you

1058
01:17:53,001 --> 01:17:58,132
You compelled me and controlled me to
say what I don't intend to say to anyone

1059
01:17:58,707 --> 01:18:00,937
You had told me nothing
that is not known to me

1060
01:18:01,043 --> 01:18:03,637
that isn't known to me for some time

1061
01:18:03,745 --> 01:18:10,981
I lived all these weeks for... 
the knife in my heart

1062
01:18:11,586 --> 01:18:15,818
I'm content to live here for his sake

1063
01:18:15,924 --> 01:18:18,620
It's the better way it must be

1064
01:18:19,361 --> 01:18:22,888
I'm sure there was anything to be done
he'd have done it

1065
01:18:23,465 --> 01:18:26,832
I'm sure he suffers as much as I do

1066
01:18:26,935 --> 01:18:29,631
Mrs. Strauss, Madam Donner leaves

1067
01:18:29,705 --> 01:18:32,003
after the opera tonight for tour of Europe

1068
